      "sedating            0.6353\n",
      "loratidine          0.6274\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "example_words = [\n",
    "    \"pain\",\n",
    "    \"headache\",\n",
    "    \"sleep\",\n",
    "    \"nausea\",\n",
    "    \"doctor\",\n",
    "    \"effective\"\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "for word in example_words:\n",
    "    show_similar_words(word)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "pSiA6qdOTIlm"
   },
   "source": [
    "The retrieved words demonstrate that the Word2Vec model successfully captured contextual relationships within the corpus.\n",
    "\n",
    "For example, medical symptoms such as *pain* and *headache* are associated with related clinical terms, while treatment-related words retrieve medication and healthcare concepts. These results indicate that words occurring in similar contexts have been mapped to nearby locations in the embedding space, validating the quality of the learned representations."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "WFEQ656rTgef"
   },
   "source": [
    "## 5. Word Embedding Visualization using t-SNE\n",
    "\n",
    "Word2Vec embeddings are high-dimensional vectors, which makes them difficult to interpret visually. To explore the learned embedding space, t-SNE is used to project selected word vectors into two dimensions.\n",
    "\n",
    "Instead of plotting a large number of random words, a curated set of medically meaningful terms is used. This improves interpretability and allows clearer comparison between symptom-related and treatment-related concepts."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 21,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "JTiBvicOMQyg"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "word_groups = {\n",
    "    \"Pain / Headache\": [\"pain\", \"headache\", \"migraine\", \"cramps\", \"ache\"],\n",
    "    \"Digestive Symptoms\": [\"nausea\", \"vomiting\", \"diarrhea\", \"constipation\", \"stomach\"],\n",
    "    \"Sleep / Fatigue\": [\"sleep\", \"sleeping\", \"insomnia\", \"tired\", \"fatigue\"],\n",
    "    \"Skin Reactions\": [\"rash\", \"itching\", \"acne\", \"swelling\"],\n",
    "    \"Treatment\": [\"doctor\", \"medicine\", \"drug\", \"dose\", \"treatment\", \"relief\", \"effective\"]\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "words = []\n",
    "labels = []\n",
    "\n",
    "for group, group_words in word_groups.items():\n",
    "    for word in group_words:\n",
    "        if word in w2v_model.wv:\n",
    "            words.append(word)\n",
    "            labels.append(group)\n",
    "\n",
    "vectors = np.array([w2v_model.wv[word] for word in words])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 22,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "AJR298OGTmTh"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "tsne = TSNE(\n",
    "    n_components=2,\n",
    "    perplexity=5,\n",
    "    random_state=42,\n",
    "    init=\"pca\",\n",
    "    learning_rate=\"auto\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "vectors_2d = tsne.fit_transform(vectors)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 23,
   "metadata": {
    "colab": {
     "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
     "height": 673
    },
    "id": "tJ5xqFb1UBkz",
    "outputId": "a4dc65c9-7723-4900-b9c1-b120ee5d73b4"
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1300x900 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plt.figure(figsize=(13, 9))\n",
    "\n",
    "for group in word_groups.keys():\n",
    "    indices = [i for i, label in enumerate(labels) if label == group]\n",
    "\n",
    "    plt.scatter(\n",
    "        vectors_2d[indices, 0],\n",
    "        vectors_2d[indices, 1],\n",
    "        s=70,\n",
    "        label=group\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "    for i in indices:\n",
    "        plt.text(\n",
    "            vectors_2d[i, 0] + 0.3,\n",
    "            vectors_2d[i, 1] + 0.3,\n",
    "            words[i],\n",
    "            fontsize=10\n",
    "        )\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.title(\"Semantic Relationships Between Medical Terms (Word2Vec + t-SNE)\", fontsize=14)\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"t-SNE Dimension 1\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"t-SNE Dimension 2\")\n",
    "plt.legend(title=\"Semantic Category\", frameon=False)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "WjzFcHOuUGMk"
   },
   "source": [
    "The t-SNE projection provides a two-dimensional representation of the high-dimensional Word2Vec embedding space. Although exact distances should not be interpreted quantitatively, nearby words generally share similar semantic contexts.\n",
    "\n",
    "The visualization indicates that words describing related medical concepts tend to occupy similar regions. For example, pain-related terms (e.g., *pain*, *headache*, *migraine*, and *ache*) are positioned relatively close to one another, while digestive symptoms (*nausea*, *vomiting*, *diarrhea*, and *constipation*) form another semantic neighborhood. Sleep-related terms also appear in a common region, suggesting that the model successfully learned contextual relationships from the drug review corpus.\n",
    "\n",
    "Overall, the visualization supports the effectiveness of Word2Vec in capturing semantic similarity beyond simple word frequency."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "rDsNJat33yVZ"
   },
   "source": [
    "## 6. Principal Component Analysis (PCA)\n",
    "\n",
    "In addition to t-SNE, Principal Component Analysis (PCA) was applied to the Word2Vec embeddings. Unlike t-SNE, which focuses on preserving local neighborhoods, PCA is a linear dimensionality reduction technique that preserves the maximum amount of variance in the data. Comparing the two visualizations will provide complementary perspectives on the learned embedding space."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 38,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "HAg5755qHsNO"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.decomposition import PCA\n",
    "\n",
    "pca = PCA(n_components=2, random_state=42)\n",
    "\n",
    "vectors_pca = pca.fit_transform(vectors)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 39,
   "metadata": {
    "colab": {
     "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
