    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Yt56Qg1JPj_Z"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 3. TF-IDF Embeddings\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "The first embedding technique explored is **TF-IDF**, the method that converts textual data into numerical feature vectors.\n",
        "\n",
        "For this experiment, the **lemmatized dataset** is used because lemmatization groups different grammatical forms of the same word into a common base form, reducing vocabulary size and improving the quality of statistical text representations."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "50KxJAw6E3SI",
        "outputId": "620b8fe0-7725-40a6-a633-57d1e8407a17"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Number of reviews available for TF-IDF: 319,934\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Extract the lemmatized reviews\n",
        "reviews_lem = df_lem[\"Reviews\"].dropna().astype(str)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Number of reviews available for TF-IDF: {len(reviews_lem):,}\")"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "CZInzc3FP7Fx"
      },
      "source": [
        "### TF-IDF Vectorization\n",
        "\n",
        "The TF-IDF vectorizer transforms each review into a numerical vector.\n",
        "\n",
        "To improve efficiency and reduce noise:\n",
        "\n",
        "- the vocabulary is limited to the **5,000 most informative terms**;\n",
        "- words appearing in fewer than **5 documents** are removed;\n",
        "- words appearing in more than **80% of documents** are ignored because they provide little discriminative information."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "DooUK7xgGA4T",
        "outputId": "a29411e8-5d73-47d0-d0d7-5ee3acd9662f"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "TF-IDF matrix shape: (319934, 5000)\n",
            "Vocabulary size: 5000\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "tfidf = TfidfVectorizer(\n",
        "    max_features=5000,\n",
        "    min_df=5,\n",
        "    max_df=0.8\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "tfidf_matrix = tfidf.fit_transform(reviews_lem)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"TF-IDF matrix shape:\", tfidf_matrix.shape)\n",
        "print(\"Vocabulary size:\", len(tfidf.get_feature_names_out()))"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "Lo6d6jLjGZV6",
        "outputId": "730d9fc2-8385-4dda-afe4-d38057c1526b"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "['abate' 'abdomen' 'abdominal' 'abilify' 'ability' 'ablation' 'able'\n",
            " 'abnormal' 'abnormally' 'about' 'above' 'abreva' 'abruptly' 'abscess'\n",
            " 'absence' 'absolute' 'absolutely' 'absolutly' 'absorb' 'absorption' 'abt'\n",
            " 'abuse' 'abused' 'abuser' 'accept' 'acceptable' 'access' 'accident'\n",
            " 'accidentally' 'accompany']\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "feature_names = tfidf.get_feature_names_out()\n",
        "\n",
        "print(feature_names[:30])"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "sdvdULk0QWq5"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Results\n",
        "\n",
        "The resulting TF-IDF matrix contains one row for each review and one column for each vocabulary term.\n",
        "\n",
        "The final representation consists of **319,934 reviews** and a vocabulary of **5,000 informative terms**, providing a sparse numerical representation suitable for traditional machine learning algorithms."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "hMv6gUKdQzm-"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Inspecting a Sample Review\n",
        "\n",
        "To better understand how TF-IDF represents text, a sample review is examined together with its highest-weighted terms.\n",
        "\n",
        "The displayed words are those considered most informative for the selected review. Higher TF-IDF scores indicate that a term is particularly important within that review while being relatively uncommon across the overall corpus."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "xvYIYiGYGtKW",
