    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "pSiA6qdOTIlm"
      },
      "source": [
        "The retrieved words demonstrate that the Word2Vec model successfully captured contextual relationships within the corpus.\n",
        "\n",
        "For example, medical symptoms such as *pain* and *headache* are associated with related clinical terms, while treatment-related words retrieve medication and healthcare concepts. These results indicate that words occurring in similar contexts have been mapped to nearby locations in the embedding space, validating the quality of the learned representations."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "WFEQ656rTgef"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 5. Word Embedding Visualization using t-SNE\n",
        "\n",
        "Word2Vec embeddings are high-dimensional vectors, which makes them difficult to interpret visually. To explore the learned embedding space, t-SNE is used to project selected word vectors into two dimensions.\n",
        "\n",
        "Instead of plotting a large number of random words, a curated set of medically meaningful terms is used. This improves interpretability and allows clearer comparison between symptom-related and treatment-related concepts."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "JTiBvicOMQyg"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "word_groups = {\n",
        "    \"Pain / Headache\": [\"pain\", \"headache\", \"migraine\", \"cramps\", \"ache\"],\n",
        "    \"Digestive Symptoms\": [\"nausea\", \"vomiting\", \"diarrhea\", \"constipation\", \"stomach\"],\n",
        "    \"Sleep / Fatigue\": [\"sleep\", \"sleeping\", \"insomnia\", \"tired\", \"fatigue\"],\n",
        "    \"Skin Reactions\": [\"rash\", \"itching\", \"acne\", \"swelling\"],\n",
        "    \"Treatment\": [\"doctor\", \"medicine\", \"drug\", \"dose\", \"treatment\", \"relief\", \"effective\"]\n",
        "}\n",
        "\n",
        "words = []\n",
        "labels = []\n",
        "\n",
        "for group, group_words in word_groups.items():\n",
        "    for word in group_words:\n",
        "        if word in w2v_model.wv:\n",
        "            words.append(word)\n",
        "            labels.append(group)\n",
        "\n",
        "vectors = np.array([w2v_model.wv[word] for word in words])"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "AJR298OGTmTh"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "tsne = TSNE(\n",
        "    n_components=2,\n",
        "    perplexity=5,\n",
        "    random_state=42,\n",
        "    init=\"pca\",\n",
        "    learning_rate=\"auto\"\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "vectors_2d = tsne.fit_transform(vectors)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 673
        },
        "id": "tJ5xqFb1UBkz",
        "outputId": "a4dc65c9-7723-4900-b9c1-b120ee5d73b4"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "data": {
            "image/png": "\n",
            "text/plain": [
              "<Figure size 1300x900 with 1 Axes>"
            ]
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "output_type": "display_data"
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "plt.figure(figsize=(13, 9))\n",
        "\n",
        "for group in word_groups.keys():\n",
        "    indices = [i for i, label in enumerate(labels) if label == group]\n",
        "\n",
        "    plt.scatter(\n",
        "        vectors_2d[indices, 0],\n",
        "        vectors_2d[indices, 1],\n",
        "        s=70,\n",
        "        label=group\n",
        "    )\n",
        "\n",
        "    for i in indices:\n",
        "        plt.text(\n",
        "            vectors_2d[i, 0] + 0.3,\n",
        "            vectors_2d[i, 1] + 0.3,\n",
        "            words[i],\n",
        "            fontsize=10\n",
        "        )\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.title(\"Semantic Relationships Between Medical Terms (Word2Vec + t-SNE)\", fontsize=14)\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"t-SNE Dimension 1\")\n",
